00:17:42,762 --> 00:17:45,096
            - BUDDY.
            - YEAH?

344
00:17:45,098 --> 00:17:46,164
 - I WANT TO TELL YOU A STORY.

345
00:17:46,166 --> 00:17:47,398
           - UH-HUH.

346
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,167
     - THERE'S A YOUNG MAN
    WALKING ACROSS A FIELD,

347
00:17:49,169 --> 00:17:50,268
  AND HE RUNS INTO AN OLD MAN

348
00:17:50,270 --> 00:17:52,236
         WHO'S PLANTING
      AN APRICOT SEEDLING.

349
00:17:52,238 --> 00:17:54,505
    AND HE ASKS THE OLD MAN,

350
00:17:54,507 --> 00:17:56,808
     "WHY ARE YOU PLANTING
       SUCH A NEW TREE?"

351
00:17:56,810 --> 00:17:58,709
     AND THE OLD MAN SAYS,

352
00:17:58,711 --> 00:18:02,647
    "BECAUSE I LIVE EACH DAY
  AS THOUGH I WILL NEVER DIE."

353
00:18:02,649 --> 00:18:04,282
     AND THE YOUNG MAN SAYS
        TO THE OLD MAN,

354
00:18:04,284 --> 00:18:06,784
      "WELL, THAT'S FUNNY,
    BECAUSE I LIVE EACH DAY

355
00:18:06,786 --> 00:18:08,753
"AS THOUGH I WILL DIE TOMORROW.

356
00:18:08,755 --> 00:18:11,389
   WHICH ONE OF US IS RIGHT?"

